  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesize, that non-optimally treated carbohydrate counting-naïve
      patients with type 1 diabetes can achieve better metabolic control by counting carbohydrates,
      and that the metabolic control can be further improved with concurrent use of Accu-Chek Aviva
      Expert. Additionally, the investigators propose that carbohydrate counting will lead to
      better quality of life as a result of fewer restrictions when eating and less variation in
      blood glucose. Finally the investigators hypothesize that the use of Accu-Chek Aviva Expert
      will lead to fewer hypoglycemic episodes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
